00:40:01.160 --> 00:40:02.680
and having a
distributed computing

00:40:02.680 --> 00:40:06.710
model for digital manufacturing,
they can accelerate

00:40:06.710 --> 00:40:09.330
the innovation in the
manufacturing process

00:40:09.330 --> 00:40:11.300
because more people
involved means that you

00:40:11.300 --> 00:40:14.050
get more perspective, and
this is the whole open source

00:40:14.050 --> 00:40:14.690
movement.

00:40:14.690 --> 00:40:17.280
Actually, collectively,
the whole system

00:40:17.280 --> 00:40:20.240
gets better and more resilient.

00:40:20.240 --> 00:40:23.220
And then there's a second
part of the question,

00:40:23.220 --> 00:40:26.440
which is important, is that it
also means that a lot of things

00:40:26.440 --> 00:40:27.380
may be open source.

00:40:27.380 --> 00:40:31.210
You might say, well, somebody
can grab it and run with it,

00:40:31.210 --> 00:40:32.720
and there's a very
nice statement

00:40:32.720 --> 00:40:39.465
by the CEO of NanoSatisfi, which
launches nano satellites using

00:40:39.465 --> 00:40:41.590
Arduino chips, which is a
mind boggling initiative,

00:40:41.590 --> 00:40:42.750
by the way.

00:40:42.750 --> 00:40:45.510
And he says, look, we use
open source technology,

00:40:45.510 --> 00:40:47.770
and we know that somebody
can take it and run with it

00:40:47.770 --> 00:40:49.780
and build their own
thing, but by the time

00:40:49.780 --> 00:40:52.640
a large company can
take an idea from us

00:40:52.640 --> 00:40:55.280
and actually build a solution,
it will take many years.

00:40:55.280 --> 00:40:58.170
By that time, we'll
be light years ahead.

00:40:58.170 --> 00:41:02.160
So in other words,
the ethos of startups

00:41:02.160 --> 00:41:04.820
is that they are
much faster, and that

00:41:04.820 --> 00:41:06.630
means when you're
smaller, you're nimbler.

00:41:06.630 --> 00:41:07.880
That's what I'm trying to say.

00:41:07.880 --> 00:41:11.510
That also means that by the
time a large company, a Goliath,

00:41:11.510 --> 00:41:13.540
tries to steal
something you're doing,

00:41:13.540 --> 00:41:16.000
but because of the bureaucracy,
it will take them so long

00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:17.970
to actually commercialize
it, you'll already

00:41:17.970 --> 00:41:20.650
be multiple versions ahead.

00:41:20.650 --> 00:41:24.940
So collectively, it's better
to share than to hoard,

00:41:24.940 --> 00:41:27.420
and that's why I say
in the 20th century,

00:41:27.420 --> 00:41:29.360
people believed that
knowledge is power.

00:41:29.360 --> 00:41:32.860
And today, power is about
sharing and finding knowledge,

00:41:32.860 --> 00:41:35.412
and that's why you come
in innocently, by the way.

00:41:35.412 --> 00:41:36.370
I'm just transitioning.

00:41:36.370 --> 00:41:38.619
People ask me, what is the
role of Google in the maker

00:41:38.619 --> 00:41:40.110
movement, things like that?

00:41:40.110 --> 00:41:42.990
The more you distribute
things, guess what happens.

00:41:42.990 --> 00:41:45.580
There's more friction
in the marketplace.

00:41:45.580 --> 00:41:49.320
There is more need for
discovery of services.

00:41:49.320 --> 00:41:51.760
As long as centralized--
this is an economic theory.

00:41:51.760 --> 00:41:53.760
It's called the
theory of costs, which

00:41:53.760 --> 00:41:56.190
is the idea that the reason
you centralize everything

00:41:56.190 --> 00:41:59.409
is that you know exactly
what's happening in the system.

00:41:59.409 --> 00:42:00.700
You have a corporate directory.

00:42:00.700 --> 00:42:02.340
You can find names
and everything.

00:42:02.340 --> 00:42:03.920
But the moment
you distribute it,

00:42:03.920 --> 00:42:06.700
everything becomes so
distributed that you cannot

00:42:06.700 --> 00:42:11.300
easily find potential partners,
so the search becomes super,

00:42:11.300 --> 00:42:13.360
super, super vital.

00:42:13.360 --> 00:42:15.270
So this is where I
get excited for you

00:42:15.270 --> 00:42:18.290
because I think that Google can
play a very interesting role

00:42:18.290 --> 00:42:21.530
by leveraging, I would say, its
core, the real essence of what

00:42:21.530 --> 00:42:24.400
it is, which is search,
and think about how it can

00:42:24.400 --> 00:42:27.300
transpose that in
this model to reduce

00:42:27.300 --> 00:42:29.644
the friction in
this frugal economy.

00:42:29.644 --> 00:42:32.060
If you do that, then the economy
becomes even more robust.

