AUDIENCE: So can you talk a
little bit more about examples

00:46:22.052 --> 00:46:25.050
that you're seeing in
this frugal supply chain?

00:46:25.050 --> 00:46:29.730
NAVI RADJOU: So what Judy is
asking is a very profound idea.

00:46:29.730 --> 00:46:36.910
Essentially, we are going to go
from just in case manufacturing

00:46:36.910 --> 00:46:38.406
model or design principle.

00:46:38.406 --> 00:46:39.780
That means what
happens in design

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:41.869
is that-- I don't
think Google does that,

00:46:41.869 --> 00:46:44.410
but some of your rivals I know
do that, which is essentially,

00:46:44.410 --> 00:46:48.280
just in case design is let's put
all the features in something

00:46:48.280 --> 00:46:50.870
just in case there's a use
case that requires the customer

00:46:50.870 --> 00:46:53.300
to use that feature,
and then you end up

00:46:53.300 --> 00:46:55.570
creating a very bloated system.

00:46:55.570 --> 00:46:57.050
As a result, the
supply chain also

00:46:57.050 --> 00:46:58.700
gets bloated because
you have to plan

00:46:58.700 --> 00:47:00.240
for all these raw
materials you need

00:47:00.240 --> 00:47:01.810
to make the product possible.

00:47:01.810 --> 00:47:05.650
So the design is where 70%
of the life cycle costs

00:47:05.650 --> 00:47:08.610
are determined.

00:47:08.610 --> 00:47:11.730
So the more you make the design
cleaner, simpler, whatever

00:47:11.730 --> 00:47:15.731
you want to call it, the more
you can have downstream effect.

00:47:15.731 --> 00:47:18.230
So I'm starting with the answer
because in the supply chain,

00:47:18.230 --> 00:47:20.200
design is the first
stage, in a way.

00:47:20.200 --> 00:47:23.830
So I call this just in case
design, which is essentially

00:47:23.830 --> 00:47:28.150
that you design just for the
70% needs of the customers,

00:47:28.150 --> 00:47:31.249
and then you
incrementally add things.

00:47:31.249 --> 00:47:33.790
So that directly comes to, let's
say, a sector like printing,

00:47:33.790 --> 00:47:35.640
because one of
the problem I have

